because I'm not am academic myself.

69
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:27,930
But mind mapping, which is also
called clustering, some people may

70
00:04:27,930 --> 00:04:32,830
know it by that name instead,
is where you take a piece of paper and

71
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:36,230
you turn it sideways and
that's really, really important.

72
00:04:36,230 --> 00:04:41,200
Having the paper sideways is essential
because what that does is that kind of

73
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,870
liberates your brain.

74
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:45,970
And it says oh,
I can go off in any direction.

75
00:04:45,970 --> 00:04:51,420
If you, if you have the paper in
the sort of standard 8.5 by 111 way,

76
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:57,600
that going to make your brain think you
need to write a list or worse, an outline.

77
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:03,950
And I really encourage students, in
particular, not to outline before writing.

78
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:08,340
And I know this flies in the face of
what many Grade 10 English teachers will

79
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:12,810
counsel you to do but the thing is,
if you think about it,

80
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:16,340
outlining engages your focused brain.

81
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:22,360
That's the part of the brain that's good
at spelling and grammar and alphabetical

82
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:28,020
order and sort of very specific tasks and
when you're writing, you want to create.

83
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:30,490
You want to think of things.

84
00:05:30,490 --> 00:05:32,790
You want to make new connections.

85
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:35,490
And that's where you really
need the diffused brain.

86
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:40,110
So to mind map take that piece of paper,
turn it sideways and

87
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:43,040
write the topic in the center of the page.

88
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,900
Then draw a circle around it.

89
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,930
And once you've drawn
that circle around it,

90
00:05:48,930 --> 00:05:53,280
then just write whatever
springs into your brain.

91
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:57,290
The thing I also like to say, and people
find this a little bit gross sometimes,

92
00:05:57,290 --> 00:06:00,155
but I say its kind of like
vomiting onto the page.

93
00:06:00,155 --> 00:06:02,250
[LAUGH] So.

94
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,371
Don't criticize yourself,

95
00:06:04,371 --> 00:06:10,299
don't second guess any of those ideas
that occurs to brain then write it down.

96
00:06:10,299 --> 00:06:12,609
So I did a mind map some years ago and

97
00:06:12,609 --> 00:06:16,377
